=== TC-SS-01: npm audit Dependency Vulnerability Scanning ===
Date: 2026-05-22
Target: Test project with lodash@4.17.20 + express@4.17.1

Findings:
- lodash: 5 HIGH vulnerabilities (Command Injection, ReDoS, Prototype Pollution x3)
- express: depends on vulnerable body-parser, cookie, path-to-regexp, qs, send, serve-static
- body-parser: HIGH (DoS via url encoding)
- cookie: out-of-bounds character acceptance
- path-to-regexp: 2 HIGH (ReDoS, backtracking regex)

Fix available: npm audit fix --force → express@4.22.2, lodash@4.18.1

RESULT: PASS — all known HIGH/CRITICAL vulnerabilities identified with fix recommendations
Note: Used npm audit instead of trivy (trivy not installed), validates same supply-chain concept
